### Product API Tests

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@adminToken = YOUR_ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN

### 1. Create Product
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Milk 1L",
  "sku": "MLK-0001",
  "slug": "milk-1l",
  "price": 25.50,
  "quantity": 100,
  "unitId": 1,
  "subCategoryId": 1,
  "categoryId": 1,
  "brandId": 1,
  "storeId": 1,
  "warehouseId": 1,
  "itemCode": "ITEM-0001",
  "barcodeSymbology": "code128",
  "barcodeValue": "ITEM-0001",
  "sellingType": "unit",
  "productType": "single",
  "taxType": "inclusive",
  "discountType": "amount",
  "discountValue": 0,
  "description": "Fresh milk",
  "manufacturer": "Dairy Co",
  "manufacturedDate": "2025-01-01",
  "expiredDate": "2025-12-31"
}

### 2. Get Products (default)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 3. Search by name or sku
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?search=milk
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 4. Filter by category and brand
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?categoryId=1&brandId=1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 5. Sort by expiredDate ascending
GET {{baseUrl}}/products?sortBy=expiredDate&sortDir=asc
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6. Update Product
PUT {{baseUrl}}/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 24.90,
  "quantity": 120,
  "status": "active"
}

### 7. Delete Product (soft delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/products/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}